ellar\nsurface, a behaviour similar to that observed for the frequency of maximum\noscillation power for solar-like oscillations in less evolved red giants. This\nallows us to provide a simple analytic prescription to predict the most-likely\ndominant mode as a function of stellar parameters. Best-fit relations for\nperiods are also provided. By applying results of pulsation models to\nevolutionary tracks, we present a general picture of the evolution of\nlong-period variability during the TP-AGB, that we find consistent with\nobservations. Models are made public through a dedicated web interface.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Oct 2018 18:01:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-24"}
